        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8433.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to R. F. Cooke, 29 July 1872</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5315.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ernest Edwards</ref> of Edwards and Kidd, producers of heliotypes prints for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 19, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7705.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to R. F. Cooke, 22 April [1871]</ref> and n. 3); the company was the Heliotype Company, which shared the premises of Edwards and Kidd at 22 Henrietta Street, Covent Garden (‘Commercial’ and ‘Streets’ sections of the <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6380.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Post Office London directory</hi></ref> 1872).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD refers to his publisher, John Murray, and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8433.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to R. F. Cooke, 29 July 1872</ref>.</note>
